                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14480286" author="paulk" created="Sat, 27 Apr 2013 21:24:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be more accurate to say that FilteredNodeChildren relies on an inherited childNodes() implementation which doesn&apos;t take into account the filtering Closure. But in any case, given &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6125&quot; title=&quot;Bugs in GPathResult.parent() and &amp;#39;..&amp;#39; notation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6125&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6125&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, should we close this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474414" author="eddelplus" created="Sun, 28 Apr 2013 01:16:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we should keep this issue for the childNodes of FilteredNodeChildren, because this (after testing) hopefully will not break anything and can be introduced short term. I&apos;d still have to rework the fix, given the additional insight gained from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6125&quot; title=&quot;Bugs in GPathResult.parent() and &amp;#39;..&amp;#39; notation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6125&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6125&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Both childNodes() and iterator() in NodeChildren should be fixed, so that they can safely be inherited by FilteredNodeChildren. That&apos;ll be cleaner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474450" author="eddelplus" created="Sun, 28 Apr 2013 01:55:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a nice clean GitHub pull request:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/175&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474446" author="paulk" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2013 05:23:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
